---
description: Core rules for the Support Ticket Management System
alwaysApply: true
---

- The ticket status state machine lives in one module:
  `backend/src/domain/ticketStatus.ts`. Do not duplicate or fork transition
  logic. `frontend/src/status.ts` is a UX-only mirror and must match it.
- Status changes ONLY through `POST /api/tickets/:id/status`. The generic
  `PATCH /api/tickets/:id` must never modify status.
- Allowed transitions: OPEN -> IN_PROGRESS | CANCELLED; IN_PROGRESS -> RESOLVED |
  CANCELLED; RESOLVED -> CLOSED; CLOSED and CANCELLED are terminal. Invalid
  transitions return HTTP 400 and must fail closed.
- Validate all input with Zod at the route boundary; use the central error
  handler with the `{ error, details? }` shape.
- Never commit secrets. Only `.env.example` is tracked; `.env` and `*.db` are
  git-ignored. `JWT_SECRET` comes from the environment; passwords are bcrypt-hashed.
- Auth: all routes except `POST /api/auth/login` and `GET /api/health` require a
  valid JWT via `requireAuth`. `PATCH /tickets/:id` and `POST /tickets/:id/status`
  additionally require `requireRole("AGENT","ADMIN")`.
- Never accept `createdById` / comment author from the request body; derive it
  from the authenticated token (`req.user.sub`). The frontend `MANAGER_ROLES`
  mirror in `frontend/src/types.ts` must match the backend role policy.
- Keep the mandatory tests green:
  `backend/tests/ticketStatus.integration.test.ts` and
  `backend/tests/auth.integration.test.ts`.
- When transition rules or the auth policy change, update the tests and
  `tool-specific/cursor-workflow/spec.md` together.
